-- Maruti Suzuki Has Hedged Six Months of Euro Currency Contracts, Seth Says
-- Vipin Nair
-- 2010-04-28T03:22:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-28/maruti-suzuki-has-hedged-six-months-of-euro-currency-contracts-seth-says.html

          
          
             Maruti Suzuki India Ltd. has
already hedged euro contracts for the April-September period to
insulate against any fluctuation in the currency, Chief
Financial Officer Ajay Seth said in a phone interview today.  
 The company has no plan to change its export strategy to
Europe, he said.  
